    "leafs": {
      "full_name": "Toronto Maple Leafs",
      "league": "NHL",
      "record": "32-36-14",
      "detail": "8th in Atlantic Division",
      "live_strip": null,
      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The Toronto Maple Leafs' season slammed shut like a frostbitten door - another year of talent squandered in the Atlantic's brutal scrum, finishing <strong>8th in the division with a 32-36-14 record and just 78 points</strong>, 31 games back and clinched for the draft lottery dustbin. Seven straight losses to end it all underscored the rot: a core that teases brilliance but crumbles under pressure, goaltending that leaked like a sieve, and a power play that vanished when it mattered. No excuses this time - the Leafs' high-society stars, led by Auston Matthews, couldn't drag this roster past mediocrity, their offensive fireworks fizzling against playoff grinders. Whispers of coaching upheaval swirl as Craig Berube's honeymoon sours, with free agency looming to reshape the blue line and that <strong>15th playoff seed</strong> lottery ping-puck dictating the summer's draft haul. Key thread? Matthews, ever the captain's burden, needs wingers who finish, not fade. <strong>Watch the lottery draw and Shanahan's first axe swing - they'll define if Toronto finally builds a winner or just another also-ran saga.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 20, 2026"
      },
