        "body": "The draft smoke thickens in Ashburn, where a 5-12 stumble left the Commanders third in the NFC East - six games back, a late win their lone consolation - yet now, with pick No. 7 gleaming like a loaded pistol, GM Adam Peters stares down the abyss of a thin top tier. <strong>Yesterday's buzz hit hard: reports swirled that Washington eyes trading down from seven to snag LSU corner Mansoor Delane while pocketing an extra second-rounder</strong>, clashing with Peters' pre-draft vow to stand pat and contradicting his presser optimism. Their board screams need - secondary shredded, line shaky despite free-agency hauls like Brandon Coleman and Josh Conerly anchoring the trenches - while mocks peg Delane or Notre Dame's Jeremiah Love as Peters' white whale in a seven-man draft scrum. Jayden Daniels, the Pro Bowl spark who dragged them to relevance, demands protection and playmakers; a weak RB class tempts no one, but deep WR waters beckon. Trade partners lurk - Jets, Raiders sniffing top-10 value - and Peters, two drafts in with four starters already, won't whiff. <strong>Thursday's curtain rises in Detroit: will they wheel, deal, or draft a savior?</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 20, 2026"
